The set of Vouchers:        V == {v1, v2, ...}                                   *)
The set of "Source" Voucher Holders : SH == {src1, src2,...}                       *)
The set of “Destination” Voucher Holders: DH ==  ({dst1 , dst2...})                  *)
vState[v] is the state of voucher 'v'                                            *)
vlcState[v] is the state of the voucher life cycle                                 *)
machine.                                                                             *)
shState[s]  is the state of "source" Voucher Holder s                               *)
dhState[h]  is the state of "destination" Voucher holder h                            *)
The state of the voucher transaction provider: VTP                                   *)
A set SHs and DHs from which the VTP has received                                     *)
“Prepared for Voucher Transfer” messages.                                             *)
vtpPrepared == {sh  : sh \in SH /\ (msg[v] = Prepare)}                                  *)
dhVTP=={h: h \in DH/\((state=Aborted\/ state=Transferred))                            })                                             
====================================================================================*)
THE OPERATIONS OF VoucherTransactionProvider(VTP) ARE AS FOLLOWS : 
The VTPSpec states that the vouchers have a valid source and destination holders.    *)
(* The transfer of each specific Voucher is possible only if all Source Holder        *)
(* (SHs) & Destination Holder(DHs) send "Prepared" message to VTP                    *)
TheVtpPrepares == ((sh \in SH /\ dh \in DH )->((vlcState[v]=Preparing/Initialized)))  *)
(* Transfer operation of the voucher is enabled if and only if all Source Holder       *)
(*(SHs) & Destination Holders (DHs)) send "Prepared" messages to VTP                    *)
VTPTransfer == ((sh \in SH /\ dh \in DH)->((vlcState[v]=Preparing/Initialized)))      *)   (* This should be the same as TheVtpPrepares*)  *)
(* Abort operation of voucher transaction is enabled if at least one Source Holder       *)
(*(SHs) & Destination Holders (DHs)) send "Aborted" message to VTP                       *)
VPTPreventsTransfer == ((sh \in SH /\ dh \in DH)->((vlcState[v]=Preparing/Initialized)))*)   (* This should be the same as TheVtpPrepares and vstate = Aborting. If both conditions are satisfied, then it allows abortion of transaction *)
(* Initial state predicate asserts that all vouchers in life cycle is at initial or preparing stage *) 
INIT == \A s\in SH /\ d \in DH (shState[s]=Initialized\/ shState[h] = Aborting)       *)(* This should be the same as TheVtpPrepares*)  
(* Type-correctness invariant ensures that no two different Source Holders or Destination holders  *)
(*(SH and DH)) have conflicting decisions. If there is a conflict then it disables actions for them *)
TYPOK == \A s\in SH /\ d \in (DH - {h}) ~ shState[s]=Initialized\/shstate[dne] = Aborting    (* This should be the same as TheVtpPrepares*)  
(* Consistency invariant ensures that if a Source Holder or Destination holder has made their decision, then it remains constant *) 
CONSISTENT == \A s\in SH /\ d \in DH (shState[s]=Preparing\/Aborted=> dhVTP[d])   (* This should be the same as TheVtpPrepares and vstate = Aborting*)   
(* Deadlock is avoided if no Source Holder or Destination holder makes their decision until all have decided *) 
DEADLOCK == \A s\in SH /\ d \in DH (shState[s]=Preparing\/Aborted=> dhVTP[d]) (* This should be the same as TheVtpPrepares and vstate = Aborting*)  
====================================================================================*)
(*This theorem asserts that all operations are well-defined, meaning none of them    *) 
(*(SH or DH)) is in a state where it cannot execute an operation. If any such condition occurs, then the resultant deadlock can be detected and prevented using DEADLOCK property defined above *)  
THM_DEFINITIONS == INIT /\ TYPOK/\ CONSISTENT  \/ DEADLOCK                                                   
====================================================================================*)   
(* This theorem asserts that all operations are enabled at their right time, meaning if any Source Holder or Destination holder send a message to VTP then it is executed *)  
THM_OPERATIONALITY == (\A s\in SH /\ d \in DH (msg[v] = Prepare\/Abort => TheVtpPrepares/\VPTPreventsTransfer)))  (* This should be the same as msg condition in VTPSpec*)  
=====================================================================================      *)
(* This theorem asserts that all operations are executed correctly. That is, if a Source Holder or Destination holder send 'Prepare' to VTP then vstate of respective sh/dh  changes from Initialized to Preparing and vice versa*)   
THM_CORRECTNESS == (\A s\in SH /\ d \in DH (msg[v] = Prepare => vState[v]=Preparing))(* This should be the same as msg condition in VTPSpec*)  
==================================================================================== *) 
This theorem asserts that all actions are correctly implemented, meaning if a Source Holder or Destination holder send 'Prepared' to VTP then it enables voucher transaction and vice versa. The overall process is correct only when the conjunction of these conditions holds true in every state of SH/DH 
THM_IMPLEMENTATION == THM_DEFINITIONS/\ THM_OPERATIONALITY /\ THM_CORRECTNESS  
(* This should be similar to all actions mentioned above*)    *)
